stories.text:
I’m looking for time series data that I can use to model vax and unvax as separate populations to calculate the rates of case/hospitalizations/death within each. Does such a data source exist?

Basically looking for data similar to that used in this study:

https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/70/wr/pdfs/mm7037e1-H.pdf
stories.title: Ask HN: Best data source for Covid outcome by vaccination status?

stories.text:
I played a lot of Capcom games back in the day. Then there was a time where they produced nothing but stinkers.

Recently they have been hitting nothing but 10's for me. RE2 remake, RE3 remake, RE Village, RE 7, devil may cry 5, these are all solid games with great innovative mechanics. Not to mention their engine is so premium and incomparable to anything else out there, even Unreal.

So how did they turn it around? How did they come back so hard with such fire?
